<subSubSection box="[199,1045,834,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,798,1290]" box="[199,1045,834,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,835,859]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
Chosen to resemble the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[677,812,835,859]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chalcolecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[677,812,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chalcolecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,798,1290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,870,895]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium-sized spiders with narrow bodies and slender legs. First pair of legs with many ventral macrosetae. Similar in general body form, fissident retromarginal tooth on chelicera and two-chambered spermathecae to 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[348,568,942,966]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chalcolecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[348,483,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chalcolecta</emphasis>
Simon
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardzi nska, J. &amp; Zabka, M." box="[636,950,938,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="437 - 448" refId="ref30513" refString="Gardzi nska, J. &amp; Zabka, M. (2005) A revision of the spider genus Chalcolecta Simon, 1884 (Araneae: Salticidae). Annales Zoologici Warszawa, 55, 437 - 448." type="journal article" year="2005">Gardziṅska &amp; Żabka 2005</bibRefCitation>
), but differs in the lateral margins of the carapace which are almost parallel instead of convex in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[789,924,979,1003]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chalcolecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[789,924,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chalcolecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[941,1025,978,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="20.[151,263,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,815]" captionTargetId="figure-411@20.[151,1436,181,823]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. Chalcolemia nakanai sp. nov. 91 female holotype, dorsal view; 92 female right chelicera, back view; 93 epigynum, ventral view; 94 cleared epigynum, ventral view; 95 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 91, 1.0 mm; 92, 0.2 mm; 93–95. 0.1 mm." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
); the thin femur, patella and tibia of the first pair of legs which are not much thicker than metatarsus and tarsus (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1095,1014,1038]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="20.[151,263,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,815]" captionTargetId="figure-411@20.[151,1436,181,823]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. Chalcolemia nakanai sp. nov. 91 female holotype, dorsal view; 92 female right chelicera, back view; 93 epigynum, ventral view; 94 cleared epigynum, ventral view; 95 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 91, 1.0 mm; 92, 0.2 mm; 93–95. 0.1 mm." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
); the presence of four pairs of ventral macrosetae on the female first metatarsus (three pairs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[908,1043,1051,1075]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chalcolecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[908,1043,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chalcolecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the presence of distinct median septum in the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[448,533,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="20.[151,263,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,815]" captionTargetId="figure-411@20.[151,1436,181,823]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. Chalcolemia nakanai sp. nov. 91 female holotype, dorsal view; 92 female right chelicera, back view; 93 epigynum, ventral view; 94 cleared epigynum, ventral view; 95 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 91, 1.0 mm; 92, 0.2 mm; 93–95. 0.1 mm." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
) and the absence of accessory glands in the vulva (
<figureCitation box="[1137,1271,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="20.[151,263,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,815]" captionTargetId="figure-411@20.[151,1436,181,823]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. Chalcolemia nakanai sp. nov. 91 female holotype, dorsal view; 92 female right chelicera, back view; 93 epigynum, ventral view; 94 cleared epigynum, ventral view; 95 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 91, 1.0 mm; 92, 0.2 mm; 93–95. 0.1 mm." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 94–95</figureCitation>
). Unpublished molecular data also indicate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[502,645,1123,1147]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chalcolemia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[502,645,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chalcolemia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[714,849,1123,1147]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chalcolecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,849,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chalcolecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct genera. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[1107,1250,1123,1147]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chalcolemia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1107,1250,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chalcolemia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Barrion &amp; Litsinger 1995" authorityName="Barrion &amp; Litsinger" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,640,1158,1182]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Gambaquezonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,335,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Gambaquezonia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barrion, A. T. &amp; Litsinger, J. A." box="[345,640,1158,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref30092" refString="Barrion, A. T. &amp; Litsinger, J. A. (1995) Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia. CAB International, Wallingford, UK, xix + 700 pp." type="book" year="1995">Barrion &amp; Litsinger 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards, G. B." box="[762,927,1158,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="103 - 105" refId="ref30407" refString="Edwards, G. B. (2009) Males of Gambaquezonia itimana (Araneae, Salticidae), with notes on females. Journal of Arachnology, 37, 103 - 105." type="journal article" year="2009">Edwards 2009</bibRefCitation>
) in the delicate body and the presence of a fissident retromarginal tooth on the chelicera, but differs in the much slender legs and the narrower body (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1422,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="20.[151,263,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,815]" captionTargetId="figure-411@20.[151,1436,181,823]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. Chalcolemia nakanai sp. nov. 91 female holotype, dorsal view; 92 female right chelicera, back view; 93 epigynum, ventral view; 94 cleared epigynum, ventral view; 95 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 91, 1.0 mm; 92, 0.2 mm; 93–95. 0.1 mm." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
); the PLEs closer to the lateral margins of the carapace (
<figureCitation box="[758,842,1230,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="20.[151,263,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,815]" captionTargetId="figure-411@20.[151,1436,181,823]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. Chalcolemia nakanai sp. nov. 91 female holotype, dorsal view; 92 female right chelicera, back view; 93 epigynum, ventral view; 94 cleared epigynum, ventral view; 95 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 91, 1.0 mm; 92, 0.2 mm; 93–95. 0.1 mm." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
); and the presence of large secondary spermatheca in addition to the primary spermatheca in the vulva (
<figureCitation box="[709,840,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="20.[151,263,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,815]" captionTargetId="figure-411@20.[151,1436,181,823]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. Chalcolemia nakanai sp. nov. 91 female holotype, dorsal view; 92 female right chelicera, back view; 93 epigynum, ventral view; 94 cleared epigynum, ventral view; 95 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 91, 1.0 mm; 92, 0.2 mm; 93–95. 0.1 mm." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 94–95</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
